(1) Successful first 90 days (deliverables/metrics)
- Weeks 1–2: Onboarding + context. You can clearly articulate the product/workflow goals, key stakeholders, and current pain points; you’ve identified 1–2 high-confidence opportunities.
- Weeks 3–6: Own a scoped project end-to-end (discovery → plan → execution). Output: a written proposal/spec, clear milestones, and stakeholder alignment.
- Weeks 7–12: Ship the deliverable and demonstrate measurable impact. Metrics depend on the area, but we typically look for one of: cycle-time reduction, quality/defect reduction, adoption/engagement lift, or operational cost/time saved. Just as important: predictable execution and crisp communication of progress/risks.

(2) How we evaluate candidates (key signals)
- Ownership & judgment: Can you take an ambiguous problem, frame it well, choose sensible tradeoffs, and push to a decision?
- Structured thinking: Clear problem decomposition, prioritization, and a plan that’s realistic.
- Execution & collaboration: Evidence you can deliver with cross-functional partners; strong written communication.
- Impact orientation: You can connect work to outcomes/metrics and learn/iterate when results are mixed.

To calibrate fit on your side: what kind of projects are you most excited to own next (and what’s one example of a measurable impact you’ve driven)? Also, what’s your decision timeline and which 1–2 criteria matter most (scope, growth, comp, location, team type)?
